.\" vim: tw=75
.TH sharedindexsplit 1

.SH NAME
sharedindexsplit - Splits a shared index file into multiple ones

.SH SYNOPSYS
\fBsharedindexsplit\fR \fIdirectory\fR [ \fInumber\fR ]

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I directory
The directory where the shared index files should be created.

.TP
.I number
The number of characters to consider when splitting the index file.

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsharedindexsplit\fR takes a list of accounts from standard input and
splits them into multiple shared index files based on the first character
of the username or, if the second argument is given, on that number of
characters.

The full documentation of shared folders with courier-imap is located at
@prefix@/share/indimail/doc/courier-imap/README.sharedfolders.txt

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I directory
The directory where the shared index files should be created.

.TP
.I number
The number of characters to consider when splitting the index file.

.SH SEE ALSO
authnumerate(1), sharedindexsplit(1), authenumerate(1), maildirmake(1)
